10/21/83  send_mail request:  print, pr, p

Syntax:  p {-control_args}


Function:  prints the message.


Control arguments:
-long_header, -lghe
   specifies that the print request is to display all available
   information from the message header including the Acknowledge-To,
   Date, From, Message-ID and Access-Class fields.
-header, -he
   specifies that the print request is to display all information from
   the message header except the Message-ID and Access-Class fields.
-brief_header, -bfhe
   specifies that the print request is to display the minimal amount of
   information from the message header.  Only the subject and the
   primary, secondary, and "blind" recipient lists are displayed.
   (Default)
-no_header, -nhe
   specifies that the print request is to display absolutely no
   information from the message header.  Only the message body line
   count and message body are displayed.


Notes:
For a complete description of the header information displayed by the
-brief_header control argument, type:
      help print_header -section notes
